-- Citi plans to add 200 new U.S. branches: report
-- 
-- Fri Apr 15, 2011 6:36pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/04/15/us-citigroup-branches-idUSTRE73E8DI20110415

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc ( C.N ) is planning to add 200 U.S. branches over the next three years and may expand into Seattle and Atlanta, Bloomberg News reported on its website on Friday. 

 The lender would add about 100 branches in California and New York, and another 100 elsewhere in the country by the end of 2013, Cecelia Stewart, head of Citi's U.S. consumer business, told the news agency. A Citigroup spokesman was not immediately available for comment after-hours on Friday. (Reporting by  Paritosh Bansal ; editing by  Andre Grenon )